Samantha Stosur defeated  Maria
Kirilenko  to reach the quarterfinals of the U.S. Open in a match
that featured the longest tiebreaker in womenâ€™s Grand Slam
history.  Stosur, the ninth seed from  Australia , won 6-2, 6-7
(15-17), 6-3 against Kirilenko, the 25th seed from  Russia  --
finishing up the 2-hour, 37-minute contest on her eighth match
point.  Stosur wasted five match points in the 32-point tiebreaker,
which Kirilenko won on her sixth set point.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
